1. In react native Javascript is handled by one thread and UI is handled by another thread.
2. UI thread and Javascript thread is communicated by Bridge.
3. Note. Even if Javascript code is blocked UI component still works.
4. Note : In reac we have a concept of pixels and percentage while in react native unit-less number in length
        ( pixel density ?)
5. import { Constants } from 'expo' : Constants.statusBarHeight is used to get the staus bar height;